n history, to bibliophile theologian Ibn Ṭāʾūs and Egyptian polymath al-Suyūṭī. But this was not Umm Salama’s only otherworldly encounter and she was not the only one to have al-Ḥusayn’s fate disturb her nights. This is their story.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aDreamsxReligious aspectsxIslam. 0aKarbalāʼ, Battle of, Karbalāʼ, Iraq, 680. 0aTenth of Muḥarram. 4aGeneral. 4aHistory. 4aMiddle East. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertGorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074330240uhttps://doi.org/10.31826/978146324210740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781463242107423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781463242107/original  a978-3-11-074330-2  Gorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK